    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the limitation is partially mitigated by the conservative acceptance bounds applied and the consistency of results across two independent laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion that the FEA framework adequately predicts ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct for the stated regulatory decision.",
